      <description><![CDATA[<p><img src="https://scontent-cph2-1.cdninstagram.com/v/t51.82787-15/642582797_18563801509024994_867465633600228676_n.jpg?stp=dst-jpg_e35_tt6&amp;_nc_cat=102&amp;ig_cache_key=Mzg0MTkyNTkxMDI5NTU2Mjc2Nw%3D%3D.3-ccb7-5&amp;ccb=7-5&amp;_nc_sid=58cdad&amp;efg=eyJ2ZW5jb2RlX3RhZyI6InhwaWRzLjEwODB4MTM0Ni5zZHIuQzMifQ%3D%3D&amp;_nc_ohc=nrH-ka3abVsQ7kNvwHBohSr&amp;_nc_oc=AdobRQg4wNWY8Hx65tN8gt8-iTn-nRBB5ULRu9LvxThmqW394exWU-8sUxtpSoHzdVk&amp;_nc_ad=z-m&amp;_nc_cid=0&amp;_nc_zt=23&amp;se=7&amp;_nc_ht=scontent-cph2-1.cdninstagram.com&amp;_nc_gid=gasANtv10cnKzYTbI_Jbhw&amp;_nc_ss=7a338&amp;oh=00_AfxXf7WgCPOWxL-kiOjZcSa00C1MwdfuXN9ELz2haF-uig&amp;oe=69CA274D" alt="Slide 1 fra @semiotexte" style="max-width: 48%; margin: 0 1% 8px 0;" /><img src="https://scontent-cph2-1.cdninstagram.com/v/t51.82787-15/642990547_18563801518024994_5604004004444474473_n.jpg?stp=dst-jpg_e35_tt6&amp;_nc_cat=105&amp;ig_cache_key=Mzg0MTkyNTkxNDA2MjA5MzU4NA%3D%3D.3-ccb7-5&amp;ccb=7-5&amp;_nc_sid=58cdad&amp;efg=eyJ2ZW5jb2RlX3RhZyI6InhwaWRzLjEwODB4MTM0Ni5zZHIuQzMifQ%3D%3D&amp;_nc_ohc=dcgeUQdA1lIQ7kNvwH9qcKN&amp;_nc_oc=AdpiS05eb0P1ToWZDgLjGLLnyRcwZZzi--QvWI5wD67TH9AwnkYkxRqmVJDSKzkkzoc&amp;_nc_ad=z-m&amp;_nc_cid=0&amp;_nc_zt=23&amp;se=7&amp;_nc_ht=scontent-cph2-1.cdninstagram.com&amp;_nc_gid=gasANtv10cnKzYTbI_Jbhw&amp;_nc_ss=7a338&amp;oh=00_AfxcMc9QpVt5W0zb8o1NI10HY2P3wQJMSNTAoy3f0vqOTA&amp;oe=69CA11EE" alt="Slide 2 fra @semiotexte" style="max-width: 48%; margin: 0 1% 8px 0;" /><img src="https://scontent-cph2-1.cdninstagram.com/v/t51.82787-15/642841673_18563801542024994_2420876588372680795_n.jpg?stp=dst-jpg_e35_tt6&amp;_nc_cat=103&amp;ig_cache_key=Mzg0MTkyNTkxNjg0NzEwOTg0NQ%3D%3D.3-ccb7-5&amp;ccb=7-5&amp;_nc_sid=58cdad&amp;efg=eyJ2ZW5jb2RlX3RhZyI6InhwaWRzLjEwODB4MTM0Ni5zZHIuQzMifQ%3D%3D&amp;_nc_ohc=rIkmf7wJqR8Q7kNvwH24dSw&amp;_nc_oc=Adogb9i9OAm3LnGPj7rnQ4tcN6e4ydcinc1ga0NPbML0kmi4SAMvH1nEC5ZtnNAnj_w&amp;_nc_ad=z-m&amp;_nc_cid=0&amp;_nc_zt=23&amp;se=7&amp;_nc_ht=scontent-cph2-1.cdninstagram.com&amp;_nc_gid=gasANtv10cnKzYTbI_Jbhw&amp;_nc_ss=7a338&amp;oh=00_AfyAoLmAjtF-6Epp8oPnRZhM48Z_sZe58D5mk6Yp30hXCA&amp;oe=69CA35A4" alt="Slide 3 fra @semiotexte" style="max-width: 48%; margin: 0 1% 8px 0;" /><img src="https://scontent-cph2-1.cdninstagram.com/v/t51.82787-15/638887107_18563801536024994_6463523778314409487_n.jpg?stp=dst-jpg_e35_tt6&amp;_nc_cat=106&amp;ig_cache_key=Mzg0MTkyNTkxNjc5Njc3NTQzMQ%3D%3D.3-ccb7-5&amp;ccb=7-5&amp;_nc_sid=58cdad&amp;efg=eyJ2ZW5jb2RlX3RhZyI6InhwaWRzLjEwODB4MTM0Ni5zZHIuQzMifQ%3D%3D&amp;_nc_ohc=x78eWE0oVpYQ7kNvwHetnix&amp;_nc_oc=AdpZPXfBPNhcAmADxj66_J_NABLxl3husPOkQf_ChgHTXuXx1CNV0ka4kUbYFVPSh-U&amp;_nc_ad=z-m&amp;_nc_cid=0&amp;_nc_zt=23&amp;se=7&amp;_nc_ht=scontent-cph2-1.cdninstagram.com&amp;_nc_gid=gasANtv10cnKzYTbI_Jbhw&amp;_nc_ss=7a338&amp;oh=00_AfxIrpYzQJfMR7ndJgg0VSDxY9jTPcaYIrCno_AP9317zg&amp;oe=69CA371D" alt="Slide 4 fra @semiotexte" style="max-width: 48%; margin: 0 1% 8px 0;" /></p><p><strong>🖼️ Slideshow (9 medier)</strong></p><p><strong>@semiotexte</strong></p><p>What if cocktail acquaintances and real-life frenemies Elaine de Kooning and Lee Krasner were secretly lovers? <br/>
<br/>
This question underpins Ann Rower’s 2002 novel, ‘Lee &amp; Elaine,’ which is getting a second life next month with a new edition by @semiotexte. In the book, Rower, the author of the 1990 essay collection ‘If You’re A Girl’ and the 1995 novel ‘Armed Response,’ predicts and parodies a raft of now-popular genres in Lee &amp; Elaine. Her autofictional protagonist attempts to pen a joint biography of Krasner and de Kooning that also operates as a journey of self-discovery. When she fails to find evidence that Krasner and de Kooning were lovers (their associates insist they harbored nothing but animosity for each other), Rower is eventually forced to write a love story between ghosts.<br/>
<br/>
In the end, the book becomes an accidental love letter—not to de Kooning or Krasner, but to Hannah Wilke, the lost peer whose death sends the lightly fictionalized iteration of Rower into a spiral; to a short-lived love affair; and to Rower’s own past and future lives. Rower’s lover’s viscous lip gloss becomes a glue—a gummy substance stretching across generations, so women who might have hated each other can become friends, those who never met can trade secrets, and those who never knew how to phrase their compliments can simply smack their lips and smile. <br/>
<br/>
Ahead of the book’s republication, Books Editor @emmelc visited Rower at her home on the Upper West Side to discuss midlife stories, artistic friendships, cemetery sex, giving gossip a good rap, coming out narratives, and more. Link in bio to read their conversation now.</p><p><a href="https://www.instagram.com/p/DVRTCVICaf_/">Se slideshow på Instagram</a></p>]]></description>
